David Keatts commented on [low] dynamic custom ads: "ads are now built from a json file that looks kinda like this:
```
[{
    "dice": [{
        "date": "2019-06-10",
        "probability": 0.1
    }, {
        "date": "2019-06-13",
        "probability": 0
    }],
    "id": "Terese Nielson",
    "image": "/img/terese_n_ks.png",
    "url": "<https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/2115225107/terese-nielsens-tokens-of-spirit?ref=6maf99>"
}]
```
(supports multiple entries)
basically, you give it an id, img src, and url, and then "dice" is a list of dates and probabilities.  on each date, the probability of that ad showing up is set (probability out of 1).  so for these short ad campaigns you can "set it and forget it"."

